@page "/getting-started"

<PageTitle>Getting Started</PageTitle>

<h1>Getting started</h1>
<p class="lead">
    Use this page as a guide for running the Blazor app locally and keeping the Just the Docs inspired
    styling in sync with your content.
</p>

<ol class="steps">
    <li>
        <strong>Restore packages.</strong>
        <p>Run <code>dotnet restore</code> from the repository root.</p>
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Run the app.</strong>
        <p><code>dotnet watch --project src/Cam.Calculators run</code> for live reloading.</p>
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Edit styles.</strong>
        <p>Update <code>styles/app.scss</code> to change colors, layout, or typography.</p>
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Publish.</strong>
        <p><code>dotnet publish -c Release</code> produces the GitHub Pages output.</p>
    </li>
</ol>

<h2>Directory map</h2>
<pre><code>src/Cam.Calculators
  Layout/             Shared layout and navigation
  Pages/              Content pages
  styles/             SASS source for the theme
  wwwroot/css/        Compiled CSS output
  wwwroot/css/        Compiled CSS output</code></pre>

<div class="callout callout-warning">
    <p class="callout-title">Remember</p>
    <p>
        DartSassBuilder runs during build. If you change SASS files and do not see updates,
        rebuild the project or restart the watch task.
    </p>
</div>
